An Act
ENROLLED HOUSE
BILL NO. 4029 By: Caldwell (Trey), Kane, and
Ford of the House
and
Hall and Haste of the
Senate
An Act relating to the State Department of Health;
transferring funds to the Barbara Weber Amyotrophic
Lateral Sclerosis (ALS) Grant Program Revolving Fund;
providing for noncodification; providing an effective
date; and declaring an emergency.
SUBJECT: State Department of Health
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
Of the Sixty-eight Million Three Hundred Forty-eight Thousand
Five Hundred Fifty-eight Dollars ($68,348,558.00) appropriated to
the State Department of Health in Section 73 of Enrolled Senate Bill
No. 1177 of the 2nd Regular Session of the 60th Oklahoma
Legislature, the sum of One Million Dollars ($1,000,000.00) shall be
transferred to the Barbara Weber Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS)
Grant Program Revolving Fund established in Section 1-580.2 of Title
63 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
be in full force from and after its passage and approval.

Passed the House of Representatives the 21st day of April, 2026.
Presiding Officer of the House
of Representatives
Passed the Senate the 27th day of April, 2026.
